text: Emeka Ononye is a Canadian soccer player who last played for Toronto FC II in the USL. ==Club career== ===College and Amateur=== Ononye played at Wright State University for four years. He made 76 appearances, scoring 7 goals. In his junior year Ononye received Second Team All-Horizon League honors and in his senior year he earned First Team All-Horizon League and was selected to NSCAA Third Team All-Great Lakes Region. In 2014, he played with PDL side K-W United FC and made 14 appearances. ===Professional=== After trialling with USL side Toronto FC II, he was signed to a contract on April 29, 2015. He made his debut on May 14 against St. Louis FC.
